Public Protector Busisiwe Mkhwebane found that Absa could be liable to pay back more than R2.2bn for an unlawful apartheid-era bailout. JOHANNESBURG - Reserve Bank Governor Lesetja Kganyago says he's studying the Public Protector's preliminary report on Absa and will give extensive feedback next week. Busisiwe Mkhwebane has found that the bank could be liable to pay back more than R2.2 billion to the ficus for an unlawful apartheid-era bailout. Mkhwebane has provisionally found that government breached the Constitution and the Public Finance Management Act.Kganyago says he s still studying the report and has already found some errors. We re checking it for factual accuracy, we ve already spotted a number of errors. We re going through the report with our lawyers and we re grateful that the Public Protector has given us an extension. (Edited by Zamangwane Shange)